"title": "8841: unfaithfulness, to people",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8841",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A breach of the trust that is expected within specific relationships, and also a failure of mutual responsibility within a community life; the breaking of the last six of the Ten Commandments.</p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness to one another breaks God's commandments</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:18\">LEV 19:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12-Exod20:17\">EXO 20:12–20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16-Deut5:21\">DEU 5:16–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:39\">MAT 22:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:31\">MRK 12:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:29-Rom1:31\">ROM 1:29–1:31</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness to promises made</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:2\">NUM 30:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:9\">NUM 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:20\">JOS 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:42\">1SA 20:42</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness in business</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:24-Matt25:26\">MAT 25:24–25:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:3-Luke16:12\">LUK 16:3–16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness to the marriage covenant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14-Mal2:15\">MAL 2:14–2:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The seriousness of marital unfaithfulness</h3>\n<p>Adultery in the OT punishable by death:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:10\">LEV 20:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:22\">DEU 22:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3-John8:5\">JHN 8:3–8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:32\">MAT 5:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:9\">MAT 19:9</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of marital unfaithfulness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:1-Judg19:2\">JDG 19:1–19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:2-Hos1:3\">HOS 1:2–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:2\">HOS 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:5\">HOS 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness among family and friends</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:5-Mic7:6\">MIC 7:5–7:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God's people may face opposition from their families</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:6\">JER 12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10\">2SA 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:21\">MAT 10:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12\">MRK 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:16\">LUK 21:16</a></p>\n<h3>Unfaithful friends cause great sorrow</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:12-Ps55:14\">PSA 55:12–55:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:20-Ps55:21\">PSA 55:20–55:21</a>JOB <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:14-Ps6:17\">6:14–6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:11\">PSA 38:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:19\">PRO 25:19</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness to Jesus Christ during his earthly ministry</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ deserted by his followers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:66\">JHN 6:66</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:32\">JHN 16:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:31\">MAT 26:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:27\">MRK 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:7\">ZEC 13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:56\">MAT 26:56</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:50\">MRK 14:50</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ betrayed by Judas</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47-Matt26:50\">MAT 26:47–26:50</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43-Mark14:46\">MRK 14:43–14:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:47-Luke22:48\">LUK 22:47–22:48</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:2-John18:5\">JHN 18:2–18:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ denied by Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:74\">MAT 26:74</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:71-Mark14:72\">MRK 14:71–14:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:59-Luke22:61\">LUK 22:59–22:61</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:26-John18:27\">JHN 18:26–18:27</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness to God's appointed leaders</h2>\n<h3>The Israelites challenge their leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:3-Exod16:8\">EXO 16:3–16:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:7-1Sam8:8\">1SA 8:7–8:8</a></p>\n<h3>Paul's friends desert him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:15\">2TI 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:9-2Tim4:11\">2TI 4:9–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:16\">2TI 4:16</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of treachery and betrayal</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:18-Judg16:19\">JDG 16:18–16:19</a> <em>Samson betrayed by Delilah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:27\">2SA 3:27</a> <em>Joab murders Abner</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:5-2Sam4:6\">2SA 4:5–4:6</a> <em>Ish-Bosheth assassinated by Recab and Baanah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:14-2Sam11:15\">2SA 11:14–11:15</a> <em>David has Uriah killed in battle</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:9-2Sam20:10\">2SA 20:9–20:10</a> <em>Amasa killed by Joab</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:8-1Kgs21:10\">1KI 21:8–21:10</a> <em>Jezebel's treachery towards Naboth</em></p>",
